<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,327,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,367,327,352]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[308,367,327,352]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">Body</emphasis>
</emphasis>
bicoloured; head, pronotum and scutellum castaneous or dark castaneous; antennae, tibial spines, costal margins, posterior parts of hemelytra, and hemelytral punctures brown; rostrum, legs, and hemelytral surface pale brown or yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,327,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,261,435,460]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[278,348,436,461]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1369,1391]" captionTargetBox="[189,1397,201,1339]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1397,195,1345]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Amnestus mendeli: (A) holotype male, body dorsal view; (B) holotype male, head, dorsal view (graphically darkened for better visibility of marginal pegs); (C – D) paramere, dorsal view (C), ventral view (D)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263596/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number box="[332,348,436,460]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Clypeus slightly broadening apicad, distinctly longer than paraclypei and apically with four long sharpened pegs; clypeal surface impunctate, transversally striated with several striae making the clypeal surface uneven; paraclypei with distinct punctures over almost their entire surfaces, with small impunctate areas anteriorly, punctures colourless and only a little smaller than ocelli; paraclypeal margins with five pegs; eyes reddish brown or castaneous; ocelli yellow or yellowish brown; ocular index 
<number box="[1014,1096,580,605]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" value="2.5" valueMax="2.6" valueMin="2.4">2.4-2.6</number>
; ocellar index 
<number box="[1260,1277,580,604]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" value="4.0">4</number>
.0, interocellar distance approximately six times larger than the distance between the ocellus and the eye.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,327,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,651,676]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">Prothorax</emphasis>
. Pronotum almost rectangular in outline (
<figureCitation box="[801,871,652,677]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1369,1391]" captionTargetBox="[189,1397,201,1339]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1397,195,1345]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Amnestus mendeli: (A) holotype male, body dorsal view; (B) holotype male, head, dorsal view (graphically darkened for better visibility of marginal pegs); (C – D) paramere, dorsal view (C), ventral view (D)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263596/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number box="[856,871,652,676]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A), its anterior margin almost straight, the lateral margins broadly rounded in the anterior half, and straight in the posterior half; callal areas almost impunctate, bearing several punctures only; transverse postcallal impression present, interrupted medially; posterior half of pronotal disc densely punctured with large coarse punctures, except for impunctate umbones; lateral parts of pronotal disc punctured with a few large coarse punctures bearing long, hair-like setae; lateral pronotal margins each with a submarginal row of 
<number box="[541,579,832,856]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7-8</number>
hair-like setae; propleuron castaneous, alutaceous; anterior and posterior convexities impunctate; prosternal carinae in profile approximately as high as labial segment II; transverse carina connecting the prosternal carinae uninterrupted medially (
<figureCitation box="[818,887,903,928]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1813,1835]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,645,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[158,1428,628,1789]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Amnestus mendeli, paratype male: (A) body ventral view; (B) prosternal carinae (transverse carina, tc: additional longitudinal carina behind the transverse carina, alc); (E) anterior femur (furcate spine indicated by the arrow); (F) posterior femur (subapical denticle indicated by the arrow); (G) lateral part of abdomen showing long adherent, shiny hair-like setae. Amnestus pusillus (C), Amnestus lenkoi (D, from Froeschner, 1975, modified): prosternal carinae (transverse carina, tc)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263597/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number box="[873,887,904,928]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B, 
<emphasis box="[923,943,905,928]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">tc</emphasis>
); additional longitudinal carina behind the transverse carina present (
<figureCitation box="[443,509,940,965]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1813,1835]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,645,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[158,1428,628,1789]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Amnestus mendeli, paratype male: (A) body ventral view; (B) prosternal carinae (transverse carina, tc: additional longitudinal carina behind the transverse carina, alc); (E) anterior femur (furcate spine indicated by the arrow); (F) posterior femur (subapical denticle indicated by the arrow); (G) lateral part of abdomen showing long adherent, shiny hair-like setae. Amnestus pusillus (C), Amnestus lenkoi (D, from Froeschner, 1975, modified): prosternal carinae (transverse carina, tc)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263597/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number box="[495,509,940,964]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B, 
<emphasis box="[542,576,940,965]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">alc</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,327,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,975,1000]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">Mesothorax</emphasis>
. Scutellum (
<figureCitation box="[483,551,975,1000]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1369,1391]" captionTargetBox="[189,1397,201,1339]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1397,195,1345]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Amnestus mendeli: (A) holotype male, body dorsal view; (B) holotype male, head, dorsal view (graphically darkened for better visibility of marginal pegs); (C – D) paramere, dorsal view (C), ventral view (D)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263596/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number box="[537,551,976,1000]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A) with basal and lateral rows of large coarse punctures; scutellar disc almost evenly coarsely punctured, punctures as large as those forming lateral rows. Hemelytral shape typical of the genus with brown puncturation. Clavus with three parallel rows of coarse punctures (
<figureCitation box="[1068,1139,1047,1072]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1369,1391]" captionTargetBox="[189,1397,201,1339]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1397,195,1345]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Amnestus mendeli: (A) holotype male, body dorsal view; (B) holotype male, head, dorsal view (graphically darkened for better visibility of marginal pegs); (C – D) paramere, dorsal view (C), ventral view (D)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263596/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number box="[1124,1139,1048,1072]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A); mesocorium with two rows of coarse punctures paralleling the clavo-corial suture and with several, almost evenly spaced, punctures in its posterior third; exocorium densely, almost evenly, punctured. Costal margins distinctly darker than the remaining part of the corium; membrane slightly translucent, whitish, surpassing the tip of the abdomen. Mesopleuron with evaporatorium typical of the genus. Legs pale brown or yellowish brown, tibial spines only a little darker; anterior femur ventrally near basal third with a stout, oblique, apically shallowly furcate spine (
<figureCitation box="[1125,1191,1228,1253]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1813,1835]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,645,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[158,1428,628,1789]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Amnestus mendeli, paratype male: (A) body ventral view; (B) prosternal carinae (transverse carina, tc: additional longitudinal carina behind the transverse carina, alc); (E) anterior femur (furcate spine indicated by the arrow); (F) posterior femur (subapical denticle indicated by the arrow); (G) lateral part of abdomen showing long adherent, shiny hair-like setae. Amnestus pusillus (C), Amnestus lenkoi (D, from Froeschner, 1975, modified): prosternal carinae (transverse carina, tc)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263597/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number box="[1177,1191,1228,1252]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
E), its length almost a half of femur diameter; subapical denticle on the ventral margin of the posterior femur strong and broad about a third as long as vertical femora diameter, bearing dorsally an apical finger-like process (
<figureCitation box="[1136,1202,1300,1325]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1813,1835]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,645,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[158,1428,628,1789]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Amnestus mendeli, paratype male: (A) body ventral view; (B) prosternal carinae (transverse carina, tc: additional longitudinal carina behind the transverse carina, alc); (E) anterior femur (furcate spine indicated by the arrow); (F) posterior femur (subapical denticle indicated by the arrow); (G) lateral part of abdomen showing long adherent, shiny hair-like setae. Amnestus pusillus (C), Amnestus lenkoi (D, from Froeschner, 1975, modified): prosternal carinae (transverse carina, tc)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263597/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number box="[1188,1202,1300,1324]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
F).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,327,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1335,1360]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Sterna brown, alutaceous and punctate, punctures bearing long adherent, whistish, shiny, hair-like setae, especially numerous in the lateral third of sterna (
<figureCitation box="[776,843,1372,1397]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1813,1835]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,645,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[158,1428,628,1789]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Amnestus mendeli, paratype male: (A) body ventral view; (B) prosternal carinae (transverse carina, tc: additional longitudinal carina behind the transverse carina, alc); (E) anterior femur (furcate spine indicated by the arrow); (F) posterior femur (subapical denticle indicated by the arrow); (G) lateral part of abdomen showing long adherent, shiny hair-like setae. Amnestus pusillus (C), Amnestus lenkoi (D, from Froeschner, 1975, modified): prosternal carinae (transverse carina, tc)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263597/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number box="[829,843,1372,1396]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
G); paramere as in 
<figureCitation box="[1057,1123,1372,1397]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1369,1391]" captionTargetBox="[189,1397,201,1339]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1397,195,1345]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Amnestus mendeli: (A) holotype male, body dorsal view; (B) holotype male, head, dorsal view (graphically darkened for better visibility of marginal pegs); (C – D) paramere, dorsal view (C), ventral view (D)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263596/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number box="[1109,1123,1372,1396]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
C–D.
</paragraph>
