<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="117" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,327,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1660,1685]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is dedicated to Dr. Howard Mendel who has collected specimens of this new species and has inspired us to prepare this paper.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="119" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,327,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,463,1732,1757]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species belongs to the group of species in which the transverse carina is as strongly developed as the prosternal carinae and is straight (
<figureCitation box="[824,891,1767,1792]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1813,1835]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,645,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[158,1428,628,1789]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Amnestus mendeli, paratype male: (A) body ventral view; (B) prosternal carinae (transverse carina, tc: additional longitudinal carina behind the transverse carina, alc); (E) anterior femur (furcate spine indicated by the arrow); (F) posterior femur (subapical denticle indicated by the arrow); (G) lateral part of abdomen showing long adherent, shiny hair-like setae. Amnestus pusillus (C), Amnestus lenkoi (D, from Froeschner, 1975, modified): prosternal carinae (transverse carina, tc)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263597/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number box="[877,891,1768,1792]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B, 
<emphasis box="[924,944,1769,1792]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">tc</emphasis>
); this group includes two Brazilian species, i.e., 
<taxonomicName authority="Froeschner, 1975" authorityName="Froeschner" authorityYear="1975" box="[199,582,1804,1829]" class="Insecta" family="Cydnidae" genus="Amnestus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lenkoi">
<emphasis box="[199,382,1804,1829]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">Amnestus lenkoi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Froeschner" box="[389,582,1804,1829]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" refString="Froeschner, R. C. (1975) Three new species of burrowing bugs found in associations with ants in Brazil (Hemiptera: Cydnidae). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 48, 105 - 110." type="journal article" year="1975">
Froeschner, 
<number box="[526,582,1804,1829]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" value="1975.0">1975</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Froeschner, 1975" authorityName="Froeschner" authorityYear="1975" box="[637,1056,1804,1829]" class="Insecta" family="Cydnidae" genus="Amnestus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pequinus">
<emphasis box="[637,853,1805,1828]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">Amnestus pequinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Froeschner" box="[860,1056,1804,1829]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" refString="Froeschner, R. C. (1975) Three new species of burrowing bugs found in associations with ants in Brazil (Hemiptera: Cydnidae). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 48, 105 - 110." type="journal article" year="1975">
Froeschner, 
<number box="[997,1056,1804,1829]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" value="1975.0">1975</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. In all other species of this genus, the carina is lower than the prosternal carinae and bowed or angled posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[1045,1111,1839,1864]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1813,1835]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,645,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[158,1428,628,1789]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Amnestus mendeli, paratype male: (A) body ventral view; (B) prosternal carinae (transverse carina, tc: additional longitudinal carina behind the transverse carina, alc); (E) anterior femur (furcate spine indicated by the arrow); (F) posterior femur (subapical denticle indicated by the arrow); (G) lateral part of abdomen showing long adherent, shiny hair-like setae. Amnestus pusillus (C), Amnestus lenkoi (D, from Froeschner, 1975, modified): prosternal carinae (transverse carina, tc)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263597/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">
Fig. 
<number box="[1097,1111,1840,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
C, 
<emphasis box="[1144,1164,1841,1864]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="117">tc</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[125,884,687,713]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,1467,1672]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="119" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[125,230,690,711]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">
<collectionCode box="[125,211,690,711]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">TABLE</collectionCode>
]
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[229,237,687,713]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">.</emphasis>
Diagnostic characters for 
<taxonomicName box="[504,595,690,712]" class="Insecta" family="Cydnidae" genus="Amnestus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lenkoi">
<emphasis box="[504,595,690,712]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">A. lenkoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[607,727,691,712]" class="Insecta" family="Cydnidae" genus="Amnestus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pequinus">
<emphasis box="[607,727,691,712]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">A. pequinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
anđ 
<taxonomicName authority="The" authorityName="The" class="Insecta" family="Cydnidae" genus="Amnestus" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="119" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mendeli" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[776,884,690,712]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">A. mendeli</emphasis>
The
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[255,396,1467,1492]" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be easily separated from both 
<taxonomicName box="[828,935,1467,1492]" class="Insecta" family="Cydnidae" genus="Amnestus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lenkoi">
<emphasis box="[828,935,1467,1492]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">A. lenkoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1001,1139,1468,1491]" class="Insecta" family="Cydnidae" genus="Amnestus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pequinus">
<emphasis box="[1001,1139,1468,1491]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">A. pequinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the additional longitudinal carina behind the transverse carina on the prosternum (
<figureCitation box="[907,973,1503,1528]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1813,1835]" captionTargetBox="[169,1428,645,1788]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[158,1428,628,1789]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Amnestus mendeli, paratype male: (A) body ventral view; (B) prosternal carinae (transverse carina, tc: additional longitudinal carina behind the transverse carina, alc); (E) anterior femur (furcate spine indicated by the arrow); (F) posterior femur (subapical denticle indicated by the arrow); (G) lateral part of abdomen showing long adherent, shiny hair-like setae. Amnestus pusillus (C), Amnestus lenkoi (D, from Froeschner, 1975, modified): prosternal carinae (transverse carina, tc)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/263597/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">
Fig. 
<number box="[959,973,1503,1527]" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B, 
<emphasis box="[1005,1039,1503,1528]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">alc</emphasis>
). Detailed differences among these three species are provided in the Table. However, characters for 
<taxonomicName box="[887,989,1539,1564]" class="Insecta" family="Cydnidae" genus="Amnestus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lenkoi">
<emphasis box="[887,989,1539,1564]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">A. lenkoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1046,1180,1540,1563]" class="Insecta" family="Cydnidae" genus="Amnestus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pequinus">
<emphasis box="[1046,1180,1540,1563]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">A. pequinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were taken from their original descriptions by 
<bibRefCitation author="Froeschner" box="[428,639,1575,1600]" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" refString="Froeschner, R. C. (1975) Three new species of burrowing bugs found in associations with ants in Brazil (Hemiptera: Cydnidae). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 48, 105 - 110." type="journal article" year="1975">
Froeschner (
<number box="[571,631,1575,1600]" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" value="1975.0">1975</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, because our repeated requests to the curator of the collections in the Laboratório de Entomologia (Instituto Biológico, São Paulo, 
<collectingCountry box="[839,909,1611,1636]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) for the loan of the 
<typeStatus box="[1134,1193,1612,1636]" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">types</typeStatus>
of both those species have been ignored.
</paragraph>
